says, nothing rests.

00:11:45.620 --> 00:11:46.760 align:middle line:90%
Everything moves.

00:11:46.760 --> 00:11:48.680 align:middle line:10%
Everything vibrates.

00:11:48.680 --> 00:11:50.090 align:middle line:90%
This is true at all scales.

00:11:50.090 --> 00:11:55.430 align:middle line:84%
From the subatomic to the
cosmic, everything is moving.

00:11:55.430 --> 00:11:58.280 align:middle line:84%
When we think about how
this applies to our life,

00:11:58.280 --> 00:12:01.760 align:middle line:84%
we see that we, too,
are always moving.

00:12:01.760 --> 00:12:04.730 align:middle line:84%
We are either moving
forwards or backwards.

00:12:04.730 --> 00:12:08.280 align:middle line:84%
We are progressing
or we're regressing.

00:12:08.280 --> 00:12:12.170 align:middle line:84%
We're either in
a flow or an ebb.

00:12:12.170 --> 00:12:15.590 align:middle line:84%
If we stop our good
practices, as much

00:12:15.590 --> 00:12:17.150 align:middle line:84%
as we might like
to tell ourselves

00:12:17.150 --> 00:12:19.610 align:middle line:84%
that we can maintain
where we're at

00:12:19.610 --> 00:12:22.280 align:middle line:84%
and just pick up later
where we left off,

00:12:22.280 --> 00:12:24.560 align:middle line:90%
this is not what happens.

00:12:24.560 --> 00:12:26.850 align:middle line:90%
Instead, we lose ground.

00:12:26.850 --> 00:12:30.470 align:middle line:84%
But when we integrate the right
daily practices into our life,

00:12:30.470 --> 00:12:32.990 align:middle line:90%
we gain and then maintain.

00:12:32.990 --> 00:12:35.270 align:middle line:84%
This is true whether our
daily practice consists

00:12:35.270 --> 00:12:39.770 align:middle line:84%
of meditation, qigong,
yoga, focused breathing,

00:12:39.770 --> 00:12:41.690 align:middle line:90%
or various esoteric rituals.

00:12:41.690 --> 00:12:43.910 align:middle line:90%
They all help.

00:12:43.910 --> 00:12:46.700 align:middle line:84%
Daily practice with
a certain routine

00:12:46.700 --> 00:12:49.160 align:middle line:84%
brings us to a certain
level, but then we

00:12:49.160 --> 00:12:51.440 align:middle line:90%
might experience a plateau.

00:12:51.440 --> 00:12:53.480 align:middle line:84%
In order to make
the next leap, we

00:12:53.480 --> 00:12:57.740 align:middle line:84%
have to challenge ourselves to
move outside the comfort zone,

00:12:57.740 --> 00:13:02.000 align:middle line:84%
to stretch and grow in new
ways while still maintaining

00:13:02.000 --> 00:13:04.310 align:middle line:90%
what has been gained.

00:13:04.310 --> 00:13:07.370 align:middle line:84%
It is key that we continue
to challenge ourselves

00:13:07.370 --> 00:13:10.580 align:middle line:84%
to the next level of
our greater capacity

00:13:10.580 --> 00:13:14.000 align:middle line:84%
by staying humble and seeking
new knowledge so that we

00:13:14.000 --> 00:13:16.460 align:middle line:90%
can continue our growth.

00:13:16.460 --> 00:13:18.500 align:middle line:84%
Along the path to
greater self mastery,

00:13:18.500 --> 00:13:21.200 align:middle line:84%
there are inevitably
obstacles we must also

00:13:21.200 --> 00:13:23.930 align:middle line:90%
look out for and be mindful of.

00:13:23.930 --> 00:13:27.460 align:middle line:84%
These obstacles are places
where we can get stuck.

00:13:27.460 --> 00:13:29.490 align:middle line:84%
And as a hermetic
principle correspondent

00:13:29.490 --> 00:13:31.670 align:middle line:90%
says, as above, so below.

00:13:31.670 --> 00:13:34.700 align:middle line:90%
Or as the outer, so the inner.

00:13:34.700 --> 00:13:37.340 align:middle line:84%
Even though the
obstacles may appear

00:13:37.340 --> 00:13:41.420 align:middle line:84%
to be from things outside of
us, they are almost always

00:13:41.420 --> 00:13:44.660 align:middle line:84%
a reflection of
something inside us.

00:13:44.660 --> 00:13:47.600 align:middle line:84%
Otherwise, we wouldn't
let them get in our way.

00:13:47.600 --> 00:13:49.670 align:middle line:84%
What obstacles do
we need to watch out

00:13:49.670 --> 00:13:54.620 align:middle line:84%
for so that we can have more
accurate perception of reality?

00:13:54.620 --> 00:13:59.390 align:middle line:84%
These obstacles come from our
biases, our judgments, fears,

00:13:59.390 --> 00:14:01.070 align:middle line:90%
and assumptions.

00:14:01.070 --> 00:14:03.200 align:middle line:84%
The things that are
within our subconscious

00:14:03.200 --> 00:14:08.090 align:middle line:84%
mind that will distort
and cloud our perceptions.

00:14:08.090 --> 00:14:11.600 align:middle line:84%
We must face and
address these things

00:14:11.600 --> 00:14:14.480 align:middle line:84%
in order to have clarity
in our perception.

00:14:14.480 --> 00:14:19.470 align:middle line:84%
This is crucial in the
path to self mastery.

00:14:19.470 --> 00:14:22.560 align:middle line:84%
We just established that only
5% of the universe around us

00:14:22.560 --> 00:14:26.730 align:middle line:84%
is made of ordinary matter
that we can observe and detect.

00:14:26.730 --> 00:14:29.550 align:middle line:84%
Within this 5%, our
five physical senses

00:14:29.550 --> 00:14:33.090 align:middle line:84%
are further limited to
perceiving a very narrow range

00:14:33.090 --> 00:14:34.690 align:middle line:90%
of frequencies.

00:14:34.690 --> 00:14:37.050 align:middle line:10%
For example, the range
of electromagnetic energy

00:14:37.050 --> 00:14:40.260 align:middle line:10%
that we can see falls within
the band of frequencies

00:14:40.260 --> 00:14:43.080 align:middle line:10%
that we call the
visible light spectrum.

00:14:43.080 --> 00:14:46.950 align:middle line:84%
Similarly, there are ranges of
what we can hear, feel, taste,

00:14:46.950 --> 00:14:48.090 align:middle line:90%
and touch.

00:14:48.090 --> 00:14:50.940 align:middle line:84%
But we know that the
full spectrum of energies

00:14:50.940 --> 00:14:54.330 align:middle line:84%
is much broader than what our
five physical senses typically

00:14:54.330 --> 00:14:56.260 align:middle line:90%
perceive.

00:14:56.260 --> 00:14:59.940 align:middle line:84%
We also have what we could
call our five spiritual senses.

00:14:59.940 --> 00:15:02.310 align:middle line:84%
This is our
perception of stimulus

00:15:02.310 --> 00:15:05.850 align:middle line:84%
coming in through the
energy field of our soul,

00:15:05.850 --> 00:15:09.570 align:middle line:84%
rather than the physical
field of our environment.

00:15:09.570 --> 00:15:12.960 align:middle line:84%
Yet the range of perception
of our five spiritual senses

00:15:12.960 --> 00:15:16.740 align:middle line:84%
also tends to be narrow
compared to the full spectrum

00:15:16.740 --> 00:15:19.950 align:middle line:84%
of energies that
we are exposed to.

00:15:19.950 --> 00:15:23.340 align:middle line:84%
What we perceive and are aware
of through our ten senses,

00:15:23.340 --> 00:15:27.150 align:middle line:84%
both physical and spiritual,
is a very narrow percentage

00:15:27.150 --> 00:15:28.980 align:middle line:90%
of what affects us.

00:15:28.980 --> 00:15:31.080 align:middle line:84%
For example, people
talk about EMFs

00:15:31.080 --> 00:15:33.950 align:middle line:84%
from Wi-Fi and
cellular networks.

00:15:33.950 --> 00:15:38.160 align:middle line:84%
We don't typically perceive EMFs
with our five physical senses,

00:15:38.160 --> 00:15:42.210 align:middle line:84%
yet we know they affect us
and we know they are there,

00:15:42.210 --> 00:15:46.560 align:middle line:84%
and research has shown that
they do have a physical effect.

00:15:46.560 --> 00:15:49.650 align:middle line:84%
Now, through science, we've
been able to detect these ranges

00:15:49.650 --> 00:15:52.000 align:middle line:90%
beyond our physical senses.

00:15:52.000 --> 00:15:54.690 align:middle line:84%
We can also observe animals
who have a sensitivity

00:15:54.690 --> 00:15:58.080 align:middle line:84%
to perceiving ranges that
are different from humans.

00:15:58.080 --> 00:16:00.300 align:middle line:84%
But just because
we aren't aware,

00:16:00.300 --> 00:16:03.510 align:middle line:84%
doesn't mean we
can't become aware.

00:16:03.510 --> 00:16:07.950 align:middle line:84%
We can train our senses to
tune into a broader range.

00:16:07.950 --> 00:16:13.050 align:middle line:84%
We can condition ourselves and
reprogram our nervous system.

00:16:13.050 --> 00:16:16.635 align:middle line:84%
Our senses are malleable
and can be adjusted.

00:16:16.635 --> 00:16:19.370 align:middle line:90%


00:16:19.370 --> 00:16:22.520 align:middle line:84%
One good case study of this
shows how blind people often

00:16:22.520 --> 00:16:26.460 align:middle line:84%
develop their other four
senses, such as hearing, touch,

00:16:26.460 --> 00:16:31.430 align:middle line:84%
and smell, to be incredibly more
sensitive than most people who

00:16:31.430 --> 00:16:33.500 align:middle line:90%
can see with their eyes.

00:16:33.500 --> 00:16:36.560 align:middle line:84%
These people have
enhanced brain development

00:16:36.560 --> 00:16:40.160 align:middle line:84%
due to their more
finely tuned senses,

00:16:40.160 --> 00:16:42.080 align:middle line:84%
and this also has
the added benefit

00:16:42.080 --> 00:16:45.260 align:middle line:84%
of enhancing other abilities,
like memory and language

00:16:45.260 --> 00:16:46.060 align:middle line:90%
capacity.

00:16:46.060 --> 00:16:49.910 align:middle line:90%


00:16:49.910 --> 00:16:53.080 align:middle line:84%
How much of our brain
do we actually use?

00:16:53.080 --> 00:16:55.660 align:middle line:84%
We often hear in popular
culture that we only

00:16:55.660 --> 00:17:00.400 align:middle line:84%
use 10% of our brain capacity,
but that is a misnomer.

00:17:00.400 --> 00:17:04.750 align:middle line:84%
The truth is we use 100%
of our brain capacity,

00:17:04.750 --> 00:17:10.569 align:middle line:84%
but most people are only
consciously aware of maybe 10%.

00:17:10.569 --> 00:17:13.180 align:middle line:84%
If we were to hypnotize
somebody after walking down

00:17:13.180 --> 00:17:18.040 align:middle line:84%
a busy street, they could have
100% recall of the information

00:17:18.040 --> 00:17:19.599 align:middle line:90%
they were exposed to.

00:17:19.599 --> 00:17:22.690 align:middle line:84%
They could even remember things
like license plate numbers,

00:17:22.690 --> 00:17:26.260 align:middle line:84%
price tags on items in the
store windows, conversations

00:17:26.260 --> 00:17:29.810 align:middle line:84%
that other people were having
that they passed, and so on.

00:17:29.810 --> 00:17:31.810 align:middle line:84%
But if we were to ask
them what they remembered,

00:17:31.810 --> 00:17:34.360 align:middle line:84%
without hypnosis
most of us would only

00:17:34.360 --> 00:17:38.180 align:middle line:84%
recall maybe 10%
of those details.

00:17:38.180 --> 00:17:41.440 align:middle line:84%
The areas of the brain we
tend to be more conscious of

00:17:41.440 --> 00:17:44.350 align:middle line:84%
are in the cerebral cortex,
or the uppermost portion

00:17:44.350 --> 00:17:45.920 align:middle line:90%
of the brain.

00:17:45.920 --> 00:17:47.920 align:middle line:84%
Our conscious decision
making process

00:17:47.920 --> 00:17:51.070 align:middle line:84%
happens primarily in
the prefrontal cortex,

00:17:51.070 --> 00:17:55.180 align:middle line:84%
the front part of the brain that
rests just behind the forehead.

00:17:55.180 --> 00:17:57.290 align:middle line:84%
However, the deeper
parts of the brain,

00:17:57.290 --> 00:17:59.650 align:middle line:84%
including the limbic
system and old brain,

00:17:59.650 --> 00:18:04.270 align:middle line:84%
are usually operating beneath
the surface of our awareness.

00:18:04.270 --> 00:18:07.660 align:middle line:84%
We like to think that we have
full control of our decisions

00:18:07.660 --> 00:18:09.070 align:middle line:90%
and actions.

00:18:09.070 --> 00:18:11.620 align:middle line:84%
But in reality, the neural
firings of the brain

00:18:11.620 --> 00:18:15.880 align:middle line:84%
usually start in the old brain
system deep within, and then

00:18:15.880 --> 00:18:19.940 align:middle line:84%
flow from the bottom
up and then forward.

00:18:19.940 --> 00:18:21.530 align:middle line:90%
What does this mean?

00:18:21.530 --> 00:18:25.420 align:middle line:84%
Well, our old brain is more of
our habitual and instinctual

00:18:25.420 --> 00:18:26.740 align:middle line:90%
patterning.

00:18:26.740 --> 00:18:30.550 align:middle line:84%
It governs our basic
survival of the body.

00:18:30.550 --> 00:18:34.090 align:middle line:84%
When we're stressed, feeling
any kind of fear or pressure

00:18:34.090 --> 00:18:37.810 align:middle line:84%
in some way, then the old
brain's survival instincts

00:18:37.810 --> 00:18:39.160 align:middle line:90%
kick in.

00:18:39.160 --> 00:18:42.610 align:middle line:84%
This sends the signals up to
the higher parts of the brain,

00:18:42.610 --> 00:18:46.030 align:middle line:84%
triggering various emotional
responses in the limbic system

00:18:46.030 --> 00:18:49.330 align:middle line:90%
and then thoughts in the cortex.

00:18:49.330 --> 00:18:51.640 align:middle line:84%
Those thoughts and
emotion then lead

00:18:51.640 --> 00:18:54.550 align:middle line:84%
us to make a decision
to act in a way that

00:18:54.550 --> 00:18:56.690 align:middle line:90%
will help us survive.

00:18:56.690 --> 00:18:59.470 align:middle line:84%
So in reality, our
higher brain capacities,

00:18:59.470 --> 00:19:03.490 align:middle line:84%
such as executive decision
making and abstract planning,

00:19:03.490 --> 00:19:08.620 align:middle line:84%
can get hijacked by our survival
instincts when we are stressed.

00:19:08.620 --> 00:19:11.650 align:middle line:84%
We call this survival mode, and
when someone's in this mode,

00:19:11.650 --> 00:19:16.980 align:middle line:84%
it is hard for them to see past
their immediate circumstances.

00:19:16.980 --> 00:19:22.220 align:middle line:84%
One of our goals in self mastery
is to gain control of ourselves

00:19:22.220 --> 00:19:26.720 align:middle line:84%
so that our animal instincts
don't hijack our higher mind.

00:19:26.720 --> 00:19:30.500 align:middle line:10%
Fortunately, we can become
more conscious and in control

00:19:30.500 --> 00:19:34.670 align:middle line:10%
by rewiring our brain.

00:19:34.670 --> 00:19:37.160 align:middle line:84%
To do this, we use
certain sensory inputs

00:19:37.160 --> 00:19:39.440 align:middle line:84%
to more purposefully
and harmoniously

00:19:39.440 --> 00:19:42.590 align:middle line:84%
stimulate the brain
to take advantage

00:19:42.590 --> 00:19:44.840 align:middle line:90%
of its neuroplasticity.

00:19:44.840 --> 00:19:48.920 align:middle line:84%
We can retrain our patterns
at the very foundations

00:19:48.920 --> 00:19:50.450 align:middle line:90%
of our brain.

00:19:50.450 --> 00:19:54.200 align:middle line:84%
Our old brain controls
things like heart rate, body

00:19:54.200 --> 00:19:58.250 align:middle line:84%
temperature, breathing rate,
and as we become more aware

00:19:58.250 --> 00:20:01.940 align:middle line:84%
of these operations, we not
only perceive the subtle changes

00:20:01.940 --> 00:20:05.090 align:middle line:84%
in our body functions
much more quickly,

00:20:05.090 --> 00:20:08.870 align:middle line:84%
but we can more easily identify
what is stimulating the change.

00:20:08.870 --> 00:20:11.420 align:middle line:84%
We become much more
in tune with our body

00:20:11.420 --> 00:20:14.210 align:middle line:84%
as an instrument of
perception, and we

00:20:14.210 --> 00:20:17.360 align:middle line:84%
identify the cause of a
stimulus much more readily,

00:20:17.360 --> 00:20:20.660 align:middle line:84%
developing that uncanny
ability to sense something

00:20:20.660 --> 00:20:22.860 align:middle line:90%
before it happens.

00:20:22.860 --> 00:20:26.000 align:middle line:84%
How does this awareness
play into our intuition?

00:20:26.000 --> 00:20:28.370 align:middle line:84%
Well, for sure, part of
what we call intuition

00:20:28.370 --> 00:20:30.800 align:middle line:84%
or the sixth sense
is simply a matter

00:20:30.800 --> 00:20:35.130 align:middle line:84%
of having more enhanced
physical sensory perception.

00:20:35.130 --> 00:20:37.230 align:middle line:90%
But there's more to it, as well.

00:20:37.230 --> 00:20:40.880 align:middle line:84%
We also have our spiritual
senses of our energy body

00:20:40.880 --> 00:20:43.880 align:middle line:84%
that can detect more subtle
energies and higher vibrations

00:20:43.880 --> 00:20:46.940 align:middle line:90%
coming in from spirit.

00:20:46.940 --> 00:20:49.070 align:middle line:84%
When we can combine a
heightened sense of ability

00:20:49.070 --> 00:20:52.850 align:middle line:84%
to perceive more with our
five physical senses along

00:20:52.850 --> 00:20:55.490 align:middle line:84%
with our five
spiritual senses, that

00:20:55.490 --> 00:20:59.240 align:middle line:84%
is when we become truly
superhuman in our awareness

00:20:59.240 --> 00:21:02.310 align:middle line:90%
of what is going on.

00:21:02.310 --> 00:21:05.870 align:middle line:84%
So what are our
spiritual senses?

00:21:05.870 --> 00:21:08.480 align:middle line:84%
These include our
perception of energy fields,

00:21:08.480 --> 00:21:12.470 align:middle line:84%
such as magnetic energy, etheric
energies, the four elements

00:21:12.470 --> 00:21:16.220 align:middle line:84%
of earth, water, air, and
fire, the energies of the aura

00:21:16.220 --> 00:21:19.340 align:middle line:90%
and higher dimensional energies.

00:21:19.340 --> 00:21:22.730 align:middle line:84%
An example is when the hairs
on the back of our neck or arms

00:21:22.730 --> 00:21:24.080 align:middle line:90%
stand up.

00:21:24.080 --> 00:21:27.350 align:middle line:84%
We may be having an
intuitive pit, a perception

00:21:27.350 --> 00:21:29.310 align:middle line:90%
of subtle energies.

00:21:29.310 --> 00:21:33.110 align:middle line:84%
This phenomenon in the body
is governed by the old brain.

00:21:33.110 --> 00:21:35.360 align:middle line:84%
Many people don't pay attention
to this kind of thing,

00:21:35.360 --> 00:21:37.520 align:middle line:84%
or maybe they
rationalize it away

00:21:37.520 --> 00:21:41.780 align:middle line:84%
and they stay unaware of what
is stimulating this response.

00:21:41.780 --> 00:21:44.810 align:middle line:84%
But the more in tune
we become, the more

00:21:44.810 --> 00:21:49.220 align:middle line:84%
we are aware of these sensations
as soon as they happen.

00:21:49.220 --> 00:21:51.710 align:middle line:84%
We can then pay
attention to the signal

00:21:51.710 --> 00:21:54.020 align:middle line:84%
to identify what's going
on around us that might

00:21:54.020 --> 00:21:56.660 align:middle line:90%
be triggering this response.

00:21:56.660 --> 00:21:59.450 align:middle line:84%
Could it be that we are
empathically picking up

00:21:59.450 --> 00:22:01.720 align:middle line:90%
on someone else's field?

00:22:01.720 --> 00:22:05.280 align:middle line:84%
Empaths often feel what
others are feeling.

00:22:05.280 --> 00:22:08.780 align:middle line:84%
But when we don't have full
awareness of our field,

00:22:08.780 --> 00:22:11.300 align:middle line:84%
we often misinterpret
the stimulus

00:22:11.300 --> 00:22:13.550 align:middle line:90%
and might mistake it as our own.

00:22:13.550 --> 00:22:16.430 align:middle line:84%
This is where empaths tend
to take on the emotions

00:22:16.430 --> 00:22:18.480 align:middle line:90%
and energies of other people.

00:22:18.480 --> 00:22:22.880 align:middle line:84%
But with greater awareness and
self-knowledge, we can realize,

00:22:22.880 --> 00:22:24.620 align:middle line:90%
this feeling isn't mine.

00:22:24.620 --> 00:22:27.140 align:middle line:90%
It's coming from someone else.

00:22:27.140 --> 00:22:33.770 align:middle line:84%
We don't have to take it on as
long as we know it's not ours.

00:22:33.770 --> 00:22:37.550 align:middle line:84%
